      • getNextTask

        public boolean getNextTask(java.lang.String managerState)
        Choose the next task In theoretical terms, it will confirm if there is a new task to be done. In practical terms, the manager waits if the vectors of each service are empty. As soon as they are not, they perform a task.
        Parameters:
        managerState - manager's state
        Returns:
        true, when the vectores are not empty

      • appraiseSit

        public java.lang.String appraiseSit()
        In theoretical terms, you will choose one of the services. In practical terms, it will choose one of the vectors, prioritizing to look for new parts, followed by alerting the customers and finally serving the customers. 0 - ATENDING_CUSTOMER 1 - ALERTING_CUSTOMER 2 - GETTING_NEW_PARTS
        Returns:
        0,1 or 2, which means the service number

      • talkToCustomer

        public void talkToCustomer(java.lang.String customer,
                           java.lang.String managerState)
        In theoretical terms, spend some time talking to the customer. In practical terms, it is a synchronization point, where the manager updates the "talkBetweenManCust" variable to true. If the variable is already true, you expect the client to respond before talking to another client. Remove this customer from the service queue.
        Parameters:
        customer - customer's info
        managerState - manager's state

      • talkWithManager

        public void talkWithManager(int customer)
        In theoretical terms, the client spends some time talking to the manager. In practical terms, it is a synchronization point where the client updates the "talkBetweenManCust" variable to false if that client is the client that the manager initiated a conversation. If the variable is already false, it means that the manager has not started a conversation yet and therefore expects the manager to respond.
        Parameters:
        customer - customer's id

      • receivePayment

        public void receivePayment(java.lang.String info)
        In theoretical terms, the manager receives payment from the customer for the service rendered. In practical terms, it is a synchronization point where the manager updates the variable "pay" to false, meaning the collection of the payment.
        Parameters:
        info - customer's info
